- **Scope**
  - Applies when committing code changes from the local workspace using Git CLI on Windows PowerShell.
  - Use for routine commits and pushes to existing or new branches.
  - **Also use** when pushing frontend repos so **AWS Amplify production builds** trigger on the correct branch.
  - When the user asks to commit/push the **core trio** (mosc-temp + batch-jobs + service together), also follow [git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc).
  - **One-shot prompt** (commit + unstaged files + release deploy): [git_commit_push_release_deploy.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_commit_push_release_deploy.mdc).

- **Pre-checks**
  - **Verify current branch**:
    ```powershell
    git status -sb
    git branch -a | Select-String "release"
    ```
  - If you need a new branch:
    ```powershell
    git checkout -b <new-branch-name>
    ```

