## **Amplify deploy: merge to release branch before push**

When the goal is to **trigger AWS Amplify** (production / satellite frontends), the push must land on the branch Amplify watches — not only the feature branch.

| Repo | Typical path | Amplify production branch | Action if not on that branch |
|------|--------------|----------------------------|------------------------------|
| `mosc-temp` | `F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp` | `release/v1.0.0` | Commit → merge/fast-forward into `release/v1.0.0` → push `release/v1.0.0` |
| `event-site-front-end-test-site` | `F:\project_workspace\event-site-front-end-test-site` | `release/v1.0.0` | Commit on `release/v1.0.0` → push |
| `event-site-front-end-template` | `F:\project_workspace\event-site-front-end-template` | `main` (no `release/*` on remote) | Commit on `main` → push `main` |
| `strapi-editorial-template` | `F:\project_workspace\strapi-editorial-template` | `release/v1.0.0` or `main` | Commit on `main` → FF/merge `release/v1.0.0` if prod uses it |
| `event-site-manager-batch-jobs` | `F:\project_workspace\event-site-manager-batch-jobs` | `release/v1.0.0` | Commit on `main` → merge into `release/v1.0.0` → push |
| `event-site-manager-service` | `F:\project_workspace\event-site-manager-service` | `release/v1.0.0` | Commit on feature branch → merge into `release/v1.0.0` → push |
| `event-site-manager` (primary) | `F:\project_workspace\event-site-manager` | Check Amplify console / docs | Usually `release/v1.0.0` or `main` per app |

**Workflow (feature branch → release) — pull, merge, resolve, then push or PR:**

```powershell
cd F:\project_workspace\<repo>
$work = git branch --show-current   # or explicit: MOSC-redesign-sub-poc-2, main, etc.

# 0) Pull work branch first (Phase 0)
git fetch origin
git pull origin $work

# 1) Commit on work branch (after secret scan below)
git add -A
# ... secret filter ...
git commit -m "feat(scope): short imperative message"
git push origin $work

# 2) Preview release merge LOCALLY — resolve conflicts before push
git fetch origin
git checkout release/v1.0.0
git pull origin release/v1.0.0
git merge $work -m "merge: $work into release/v1.0.0 for deploy"

# If conflicts: resolve files, git add, git commit (merge --continue)
# If CRLF-only drift and no real conflicts: git reset --hard $work

# 3) Push release OR open PR if protected
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = "true"
git push origin release/v1.0.0
Remove-Item Env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY
git checkout $work
```

**If `git push origin release/v1.0.0` is rejected** (protected branch / PR required):

```powershell
# Work branch must already be pushed
gh pr create --base release/v1.0.0 --head $work `
  --title "merge: $work into release/v1.0.0 for deploy" `
  --body "Automated release sync. Local merge conflicts resolved: <yes/no>."

# Check PR mergeability; merge if clean
gh pr view --json mergeable,mergeStateStatus,url
gh pr merge <number> --merge --delete-branch=false
```

- **DO:** Resolve merge conflicts **locally** on `release/v1.0.0` (or on work branch during pull) **before** push or PR.
- **DO:** Open a **pull request** when direct push to `release/v1.0.0` is blocked; attempt `gh pr merge` after conflicts are resolved.
- **DON'T:** Push only the work branch and assume prod deployed.
- **DON'T:** Force-push `release/v1.0.0` without explicit user approval.

