## **Include untracked (unversioned) files — with categorization**

When the user asks to **add unversioned files**, stage everything **after** secret filtering — not only modified tracked files (same as the unstaged/untracked workflow above).

```powershell
git status -sb
git add -A
git diff --cached --name-only
```

**Categorize staged paths before commit:**

| Category | Examples | Usually commit? |
|----------|----------|-----------------|
| App / feature code | `src/**`, `components/**` | ✅ Yes |
| Backend Java (Spring) | `src/main/java/**`, `src/test/java/**`, `src/main/resources/**` | ✅ Yes — include when porcelain shows ` M` |
| Cursor rules | `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | ✅ Yes |
| Docs / runbooks | `documentation/**`, `*.html` PRDs | ✅ Yes |
| Migration scripts | `scripts/mosc-in-migration/**` | ✅ Yes (env vars for DB, not hardcoded prod secrets) |
| Manifest / map JSON | `url-list.*.json`, `*-category-map.json` | ✅ Yes (metadata/URLs) |
| SQL refresh artifacts | `export.sql`, `*.ordered.sql`, `sequence_fix_inserts/**` | ✅ Yes (unless gitignored) |
| Env **templates** | `*.env.example`, `database_target.*.env.example` | ✅ Yes (placeholders only) |
| Local caches | `.mosc-downloads/`, `**/screenshots/` | ❌ No — should be gitignored |
| Build artifacts | `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo`, `.next/` | ❌ No — gitignore or skip |
| **Secrets / credentials** | See blocklist below | ❌ **Never** |

